Description: An 'R' toolkit for copy number analysis and trisomy prediction in non-invasive prenatal testing (NIPT), built on the 'duckhts' extension for 'DuckDB'.
            Provides a high-performance implementation of the 'WisecondorX' convert, newref, and predict stages following Raman et al. (2019) <doi:10.1093/nar/gky1263>, as well as a port of the 'NIPTeR' binning and statistical layer.
            Includes SeqFF fetal-fraction estimation support derived from Kim et al. (2015) <doi:10.1002/pd.4615>.
            BAM/CRAM files are read via 'Rduckhts' without requiring 'pysam' or 'Rsamtools'.
            Intermediate results are written in language-agnostic bgzipped BED format, queryable by any tabix-aware tool or directly by 'DuckDB'.
            Optional conformance testing against the official 'wisecondorx' bioconda package is available via 'condathis' and 'reticulate'; no Python installation is required at runtime.
Imports: Rduckhts(>= 1.1.7.9000), Rcpp, stats, utils, DNAcopy, DBI, duckdb, mclust, S7 (>= 0.2.0), data.table
